job_description.133:
Nephrology Clinical Specialist, Valley View
General Information
Job Title:
Nephrology Clinical Specialist
Location:
9555 Rockside Road
Valley View, OH, 44125
United States
Employee Type:
Full Time
Brief Description
The Nephrology Clinical Specialist functions as the coordinator of patient care and collaborates with other care providers and team members to provide safe, quality patient care. This position functions as the patient teacher and advocate, provides requested information, ensures that informed consent is obtained and understood for treatment decisions and promotes patient independence.
PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITES:
The Nephrology Clinical Specialist actively participates in continuing education, quality assessment and improvement, and review/clinical application of research findings. The Nephrology Clinical Specialist is involved in
Facility staff education;
Patient education;
Facility audits;
Performance Improvement initiatives;
Hemodialysis;
Functions as vascular access coordinator; and
Performs similar or related duties as requested or directed.

JOB REQUIREMENTS:
Education
BS in Nursing; MSN preferred;
Current State Nursing license;
CNN or CDN certification preferred or obtained within one year of date of hire; and
BLS certification required.
Experience
At least 5 years clinical hemodialysis nursing experience;
Chronic dialysis experience;
Training/Teaching experience;
Current State driver’s license and insurance; and
Home hemodialysis experience preferred.
Skills
Assess patient status and take appropriate action;
Understanding of principles of adult learning;
Basic PC skills and proficiency in MicroSoft Office Suite;
Experience with electronic medical record documentation;
Nx Stage Machine experience;
Exemplary interpersonal skills; able to effectively communicate (verbal and written) with diverse backgrounds and different organizational levels;
Able to define problems and present solutions; and
Able to influence and develop collaborative, sustainable relationships.

LICENSES, CERTIFICATIONS:
Valid State Nursing License; and
Current BLS certification.

PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS:
Able to sit and work at computer for extended periods of time;
Walk, sit, lift no more than 50 pounds;
Must be able to identify and differentiate colors; and
Must be willing to travel to network facilities and sites as needed.
